snippet.textDisplay: The first time I got French Onion soup was at a local restaurant. Unfortunately, the bread they used sogged up too quickly, and turned to a mush that mixed in with the rest of the soup. It turned me off from it altogether, which is a bit of a bummer now that I know that’s not how it’s supposed to be made. Now I REALLY want to try a French onion soup done right, and hopefully this will provide me with a much better, much more correct first impression.
snippet.textOriginal: The first time I got French Onion soup was at a local restaurant. Unfortunately, the bread they used sogged up too quickly, and turned to a mush that mixed in with the rest of the soup. It turned me off from it altogether, which is a bit of a bummer now that I know that’s not how it’s supposed to be made. Now I REALLY want to try a French onion soup done right, and hopefully this will provide me with a much better, much more *correct* first impression.
